result.execSummary:
The defendant Tianna N. Mizener was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).
  • Possess Drug Paraphernalia, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
[MK] cases #15CF207, #15CM351, #16CM196 called at 2:31pm.
Defendant Tianna N. Mizener in court, in custody, with Attorney Sylvie H Dahnert.   DA Susan Happ appears for the State of Wisconsin until 3:09pm when ADA Brookellen Teuber substitutes in appearing for the State.  

Plea Hearing is held in Case #16CM196:
--Maximum penalties recited; Constitutional rights reviewed; plea of " Guilty " entered on Counts #1 & #3; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; 
--the Court accepts the plea, finds Ms. Mizener guilty of Counts #1 & #3, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.
--Domestic Abuse finding is made.
--Repeater finding is made. 
--On Motion of the State, the Court reads-in and dismisses Count #2. 

Sentencing arguments are given by counsel on all three cases.
Ms. Mizener makes a statement. 

SENTENCES: 

On Case #15CF207-Count #1, the Court sentences Ms. Mizener to: 
--serve 9  months in Jefferson County Jail, with Huber privileges including for employment, mental health treatment, AODA treatment and family care subject to the Sherrif's rules on Huber; to commence forthwith
On Case #15CF207-Count #2, the Court sentences Ms. Mizener to:
--serve 2  months in Jefferson County Jail, with Huber privileges for the same purposes, consecutive to Count #1; 
On Case #15CF207-Count #3, the Court sentences Ms. Mizener to:
--serve 6 months in Jefferson County Jail, with Huber privileges for the same purposes; consecutive to Counts #1 and #2
On Case #15CF207-Count #4, the Court sentences Ms. Mizener to:
--serve 1 month in Jefferson County Jail, with Huber privileges for the same purposes; consecutive to Counts #1, #2, and #3

Days credit for time already served given:  118 days
The Court orders payment of any outstanding costs, fees, assessments, surcharges;  this amount is to be entered as a civil judgment 
------------------------------------------------------------

On Case #15CM351-Count #1, the Court sentences Ms. Mizener to:
--serve 1 month in Jefferson County Jail, with Huber privileges including for employment, mental health treatment, AODA treatment and family care subject to the Sherrif's rules on Huber; to commence forthwith concurrent with Case #15CF207 

On Case #15CM351-Count #2, the Court sentences Ms. Mizener to:
--serve 6 months in theJefferson County Jail, with Huber privileges for the same purposes; to commence forthwith, concurrent to Case #15CF207 

Days credit for time already served given: 117 days
The Court orders payment of any outstanding costs, fees, assessments, surcharges; this amount is to be entered as a civil judgment 
----------------------------------------------------------------

On Case #16CM196-Count #1, the Court sentences Ms. Mizener to 18 months, with an Initial Term of Confinement in Prison of 1  year, and the maximum time to serve on Extended Supervision of 6 months.  This sentence is consecutive to any other previously imposed sentences. 
On Case #16CM196-Count #3, the Court sentences Ms. Mizener to 18 months, with an Initial Term of Confinement in Prison of 1  year, and the maximum time to serve on Extended Supervision of 6 months.  This sentence is consecutive to Count #1 and any other previously imposed sentences. 
The Court finds that Ms. Mizener is  eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program "Boot Camp".
The Court finds that Ms. Mizener is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.
Days credit for time already served:  0 days. 

The Court STAYS these sentences and places Ms. Mizener on Probation for three years, concurrent with Cases #15CF207 and #15CM351,  with conditions: 
--to undergo any assessement, treatment and counseling as required by the Agent
--no contact with Khristopher Arsenty
--no possession of dangerous weapons
--not to commit any acts of violence or make any threats 
--no presence in bars, taverns, liquor stores
--no possession or consumption of alcohol 
--no possession or consumption of illegal drugs
--to take all prescription medications only as prescribed 
--to pay costs, fees, assessments and surcharges including the DNA surcharge on each count and including the Domestic Abuse surcharge on Count #1 
recess 3:10pm.
Attorney Sylvie Dahnert
